    "text": "WarMonitor The Strait of Hormuz was effectively a free passageway before the war. Now Iran is deciding who gets through and making ships buy tickets to do it, boosting its leverage over global energy, while funding its military and proxies in the process. The NYT is reporting that Iran, in addition to gaining administrative control over the Strait of Hormuz, will now charge $2m per ship for safe passage, which it will split with Oman. It was free pre-war. Trump & Netanyahu have increased Iranian leverage over the global economy. - Adam Schwarz tweet",
